<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="436" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="436">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="436">Etymology.</emphasis>
This new specific epithet is derived from the Latin word “procerulus”, referring to the short protuberance between two aedeagal shaft lobes.
</paragraph>
